      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor category.",
      "rationale": "Formal uncertainty propagation for model inputs is not required at MRL 2. Nominal values for fluid properties and geometric dimensions were used, consistent with the experimental test conditions and manufacturer tolerances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor category.",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterisation of test sample variability is not required at MRL 2. The FDA benchmark dataset provides a single well-characterised geometry, and sample-to-sample variability is addressed through the design tolerance sensitivity study rather than statistical sampling."
